featured_reviews.review_id: A very beautiful mosque. Nice space for wazu. Also very clean and organised. The interior is also amazing. It's so good to see people of all age groups - young kids and elderly offer the daily prayers here. Juma khutba begins at 1:35 pm. On Friday a lot people offer prayer here and despite it's huge area, it becomes challenging for one to find a good spot if one reaches late  I often offer my prayers here as this is one of the closest mosque to my house. Definitely go and offer a prayer here if you're visiting Khargone!
